item.title: Compiler Error
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

  1. It’s not your source code. You did not type every keystroke, you did not develop the client, the code is not yours. Any additional code you add to the source is yours, but the client is not.
  2. It’s not delta. There is no such thing as a “Delta client”. The Client is the RuneScape 2 client, developed my Jagex, revision 317. “Delta” refers to the (unnecessary) modifications that were made to the client, in order to be compatible with the (unnecessarily modified) protocol.
  3. If you have a problem, what would you do to fix it?

Read full topic

By “WHATS WRONG WITH IT???”, I’m assuming that you still don’t understand what the problem is. If you can’t deduce what the problem is, with a human, and machine telling you exactly what the problem is, then there’s really nothing anyone can do.

Why are you so eager to finish your “source” (well, it’s not really your’s)? (Also, you should clarify which source you are referring to. Due to my previous experience with both server, and client, I inferred that it was the client source.)[/quote]

  1. It is my source!
  2. It’s delta but coded from scratch by me
  3. IVE NEVER HAD A PROBLEM LIKE THIS :@
